...and I'm telling you there are people here I like for this.

156
00:10:10,328 --> 00:10:12,387
好极了。就那样吗？你就是这样帮我解决 问题的吗？
Great. That's it? That's what you got for me?

157
00:10:12,564 --> 00:10:14,589
嘿，你相信吗？
Hey, you believe this?

158
00:10:14,766 --> 00:10:17,064
12年来，我一直都是你们肯纳、巴赫 事务所的客户
I have been a client at Kenner, Bach for 12 years!

159
00:10:17,235 --> 00:10:20,966
你认为我每月给你们付钱就是为了 有朝一日能出庭受审？
You think I paid that retainer every month for a place at the back of the line?

160
00:10:21,140 --> 00:10:24,439
格林先生，你在周日晚上离开一起事故的现场…
Mr. Greer, you left the scene of an accident on a slow weeknight...

161
00:10:24,610 --> 00:10:26,805
…离州警局只有6英里远
...six miles from the state police barracks.

162
00:10:26,979 --> 00:10:29,209
如果真要受审的话，你也快了
If there's a line, you're right up front.

163
00:10:29,381 --> 00:10:32,248
我随时都可以再找个律师，我不需要你了
I can get a lawyer any time I want. I don't need you for that.

164
00:10:32,418 --> 00:10:36,320
我们在这儿傻坐了45分钟就等来了这么 一个白痴建议！
We're not sitting here for 45 minutes waiting for a goddamn referral!

165
00:10:36,489 --> 00:10:38,252
我不知道沃尔特给了你什么承诺…
I don't know what Walter promised you...

166
00:10:38,425 --> 00:10:41,883
一位天才员工！沃尔特在电话里是这么说的 就在20分钟前
A miracle worker! That's Walter on the phone, 20 minutes ago.

167
00:10:42,062 --> 00:10:45,156
原话要听么，啊？“挺住，我会派一个天才来帮助你”
Direct quote, okay? "Hang tight. I'm sending you a miracle worker."

168
00:10:45,332 --> 00:10:46,959
- 喔，那他说错了 - 哪儿说错了？
- Well, he misspoke. - About what?

169
00:10:47,133 --> 00:10:49,727
关于你是公司的救火员那部分？ 还是你根本就不在行?
That you're the firm's fixer? Or that you're good at it?

170
00:10:49,903 --> 00:10:51,370
埃里奥特
Elliot.

171
00:10:51,772 --> 00:10:54,832
那个家伙突然跑出来！在大马路上！
The guy was running! In the street!

172
00:10:55,009 --> 00:10:59,742
你设想一下，大雾、路灯、还有那些转弯…
You take that, you add the fog, you add the lamps, you add the angle...

173
00:11:01,249 --> 00:11:04,741
那个家伙大半夜的在街上跑个什么劲儿啊？！
What the fuck is he doing running in the middle of the street at midnight?!

174
00:11:04,919 --> 00:11:07,114
你倒是说呀！
You answer me that!

175
00:11:20,435 --> 00:11:22,835
说车被人偷了怎么样？
What if someone had stolen the car?

176
00:11:25,942 --> 00:11:27,170
这种事常有的
Happens all the time.

177
00:11:27,343 --> 00:11:29,436
警察们最喜欢处理这种交通肇事逃逸
Cops like hit-and-runs.

178
00:11:29,612 --> 00:11:31,637
他们会快速利落地去办
They work them hard, they clear them fast.

179
00:11:31,814 --> 00:11:35,011
现在犯罪现场调查部门正在从防撞护栏 取走油漆样本
Right now there's a B.C.I. Unit pulling paint chips off a guard rail.

180
00:11:35,184 --> 00:11:38,517
明天，他们就会开始寻找谁拥有涂有这种 定制颜料的
Tomorrow, they're gonna be looking for the owner of a custom-painted...

181
00:11:38,688 --> 00:11:40,918
…那辆手排档美洲虎XJ-12
...hand-rubbed Jaguar XJ-12.

182
00:11:41,091 --> 00:11:42,683
还有你撞到的那个家伙？
And the guy you hit?

183
00:11:42,860 --> 00:11:46,227
如果他看到了车牌的话，就更快了
If he got a look at the plates, it won't even take that long.

184
00:11:49,433 --> 00:11:51,162
这样就玩完了
There's no play here.

185
00:11:51,969 --> 00:11:54,301
再没有什么拐弯，也没有放香槟的房间
There's no angle. There's no champagne room.

186
00:11:54,471 --> 00:11:57,133
我也不是什么天才，我就是个看门的
I'm not a miracle worker, I'm a janitor.

187
00:11:57,809 --> 00:11:59,367
道理很简单
The math on this is simple.

188
00:11:59,544 --> 00:12:02,536
麻烦越少，我处理起来就越容易
The smaller the mess, the easier it is for me to clean up.

189
00:12:03,682 --> 00:12:07,812
警察打来的，是吗？
That's the police, isn't it?

190
00:12:07,986 --> 00:12:09,385
不是
No.

191
00:12:10,221 --> 00:12:11,882
他们是不会打的
They don't call.

192
00:12:16,629 --> 00:12:17,994
喂
Hello.

193
00:12:19,065 --> 00:12:21,363
杰瑞，我是麦克・克莱顿
Jerry, it's Michael Clayton.

194
00:12:21,534 --> 00:12:24,002
对，是的，不好意思吵醒你了
Yeah, look, I'm sorry to wake you up.

195
00:12:24,337 --> 00:12:27,067
不，我在你的隔壁
No. I'm in the neighborhood.

196
00:12:28,008 --> 00:12:29,305
你有笔吗？
You got a pen?

197
00:16:02,925 --> 00:16:04,925
四天前

198
00:16:11,812 --> 00:16:13,905
妈妈，我的牌在哪儿？
Mom, where's my cards?

199
00:16:18,953 --> 00:16:20,784
我的牌在哪儿呢？
Where's my cards?

200
00:16:35,003 --> 00:16:36,334
我的另一幅牌在这儿不？
Is my other deck in here?

201
00:16:36,504 --> 00:16:37,903
你吃了吗？
Did you eat?

202
00:16:38,073 --> 00:16:39,973
爸爸已经在下面等着了
Dad's down there waiting already.

203
00:16:40,142 --> 00:16:42,007
洗手间里有几副牌
There were cards in our bathroom.

204
00:16:42,178 --> 00:16:43,440
吃了，我吃的瓦夫饼
Yes, I had a waffle.

205
00:16:43,613 --> 00:16:46,480
那怎么可能，家里的瓦夫饼早就吃完了
Since we're out of waffles, I don't see how that's possible.

206
00:16:46,649 --> 00:16:47,980
那是个奇迹
It's a miracle.

207
00:16:51,754 --> 00:16:53,278
带了手套没？
Gloves?

208
00:17:00,097 --> 00:17:01,086
亨利！
Henry!

209
00:17:05,869 --> 00:17:07,268
快点
Come on.

210
00:17:09,272 --> 00:17:10,603
上车
Get in.

211
00:17:12,877 --> 00:17:14,208
坐好了？
Got it?

212
00:17:20,051 --> 00:17:22,611
因此实际上没人能确定他们身处何地…
So no one's even sure exactly where they are...

213
00:17:22,787 --> 00:17:25,950
…因为那里没有边界没有地标或其它什么标记
...because there's no borders or landmarks or anything.

214
00:17:26,125 --> 00:17:28,855
至于城镇么？那根本算不上什么城镇
And the town? It's not even a town really.

215
00:17:29,028 --> 00:17:32,225
那只不过是个大家聚在一起藏起来的小营地
It just is this camp where all these people have gathered to hide.

216
00:17:32,398 --> 00:17:33,387
好
Right.

217
00:17:33,565 --> 00:17:37,023
所有这些逃兵和被军队赶出来的人
All these deserters and guys that got cut off from their armies.

218
00:17:37,202 --> 00:17:40,365
所有这些人都躲在森林里，努力活下去
All these people that are hiding in the woods, trying to stay alive.

219
00:17:40,539 --> 00:17:42,439
这就是他们归宿
This is where they all came.

220
00:17:42,609 --> 00:17:45,601
那里有盗贼、黑魔导士、佣兵…
There's Thieves, Gray Mages, Unbidden Warriors...

221
00:17:45,779 --> 00:17:47,804
…暗禽、河童、还有穴居魔
...Dark Avians, Riverwynders and Sappers.

222
00:17:47,981 --> 00:17:51,144
- 像这样的角色一共有15种，明白么？ - 明白
- There's, like, 15 different characters, okay? - Okay.

223
00:17:51,618 --> 00:17:53,347
谁都没有盟友
And nobody has any alliances.

224
00:17:53,520 --> 00:17:56,785
你甚至不能告诉别人你是谁，因为你不知道…
You can't even say who you are because, you don't know...

225
00:17:56,956 --> 00:17:58,947
…现在和你说话的这个人…
...maybe the person you're talking to...

226
00:17:59,126 --> 00:18:01,617
会不会就是你战场上的宿敌
...maybe they're like your mortal enemy in the wars.

227
00:18:01,796 --> 00:18:04,492
所以那里的每个人都只能自顾自
So it's just completely like everybody for themselves.

228
00:18:04,665 --> 00:18:05,996
听起来好耳熟啊
Sounds familiar.

229
00:18:06,167 --> 00:18:09,102
真的很棒，真的，你该读读
It's really good. I'm serious, you should really read it.

230
00:18:09,270 --> 00:18:12,433
好的，不过我看完了以后 估计你就会迷上了什么别的玩意儿
Right. But by the time I finish it, you'll be on to something else.

231
00:18:12,606 --> 00:18:15,370
- 你敢和我打赌吗？ - 不知道，你想赌多少？
- How much you wanna bet? - I don't know. How much you got?

232
00:18:16,111 --> 00:18:18,375
- 乘车卡带了么？ - 放储物柜里了
- You got your bus pass? - It's in my locker.

233
00:18:18,547 --> 00:18:21,414
你根本就不打算看它，对吗？
You're not even gonna look at it, are you?

234
00:18:21,583 --> 00:18:23,016
- 那本书吗？ - 是的
- The book? - Yes.

235
00:18:23,185 --> 00:18:24,584
星期六把它带来，我会…
Bring it on Saturday, I'll...

236
00:18:24,753 --> 00:18:27,984
我早就带了，放在你厨房里了，红色封面的
I did already. I left it in your kitchen. It's got a red cover.

237
00:18:28,156 --> 00:18:29,282
好吧
Okay.

238
00:18:29,459 --> 00:18:31,859
好吧，到了
Well, here we go.

239
00:18:32,028 --> 00:18:34,724
去吧，好好教教那些人，知道么？
Go. Teach these people something, would you?

240
00:18:38,835 --> 00:18:41,360
- 回见，爸爸 - 好的，孩子
- See you later, Dad. - Yeah, kiddo.

241
00:18:43,473 --> 00:18:44,906
谢谢
Thanks.

242
00:18:51,181 --> 00:18:54,708
第52号拍品，各种各样的搅拌碗，什么型号都有
Lot 52, lot of assorted mixing bowls, assorted sizes.

243
00:18:54,885 --> 00:18:57,854
30美元起，30美元，有人出30美元了
Thirty dollars to start. Thirty dollars. Thirty dollars I have.

244
00:18:58,021 --> 00:19:01,115
你可以出价40，40了，50，后面有人出60了
You can get me to 40. I got 40. And 50. Sixty dollars back there.

245
00:19:01,292 --> 00:19:03,522
现在60，有人出70吗？70了
Sixty dollars, get me to 70. I got 70 dollars.

246
00:19:03,695 --> 00:19:06,220
70美元，现在70了，那里有人出80
Seventy dollars, I have now, 70. Eighty dollars there.

247
00:19:06,397 --> 00:19:08,797
80，这位先生出80，80美元
Eighty dollars, this gentleman here. Eighty dollars.

248
00:19:08,967 --> 00:19:11,697
90美元了，还有人出100吗？100了
Ninety dollars there. Give me 100. One hundred I have now.

249
00:19:23,315 --> 00:19:25,613
他跟我说你还差点儿
He says you're still gonna be short.

250
00:19:27,987 --> 00:19:29,511
差多少?
How short?

251
00:19:29,688 --> 00:19:33,089
6万块，加上扣点，7万5
Sixty. Plus the points, 75 thousand.

252
00:19:33,260 --> 00:19:36,320
- 那就是酒和其他东西的价钱？ - 你觉得该是多少？
- That's liquor and everything? - What'd you think it was gonna be?

253
00:19:36,496 --> 00:19:39,488
我不知道，可能更少，三两万吧
I don't know. Less. Thirty. Twenty.

254
00:19:39,666 --> 00:19:43,534
他用了1500块就买走了我那四千块的冰箱
He took 1500 on a refrigerator I paid four grand for.

255
00:19:43,703 --> 00:19:45,330
你开个价
Make a bid.

256
00:19:47,073 --> 00:19:49,564
你不会告诉我说你连7万5都没有吧？
Are you telling me you don't have the 75 thousand?

257
00:19:49,744 --> 00:19:51,803
说真的，没有
Just lying around, no.

258
00:19:53,881 --> 00:19:56,406
我们都知道这事实际上我该找你弟弟谈
We both know it's your brother I should be talking to.

259
00:19:56,584 --> 00:19:57,608
算了吧
Forget that.

260
00:19:57,785 --> 00:20:02,085
麦克，你看，你要帮他收拾残局 这是你自己选的
Michael, look, you wanna front this, that's up to you.

261
00:20:02,256 --> 00:20:05,487
但是债务还清之前，提米依然是欠款人
But Timmy's name stays in the book till we're clear.

262
00:20:05,961 --> 00:20:10,261
如果我知道他在哪儿，我就没必要这么 一直问下去了
If I know where he is, I don't have to keep asking.

263
00:20:10,432 --> 00:20:14,129
他呆在远郊，他老婆把他领回来了 但我不知道他在哪儿
He's upstate. His wife took him back. I don't know where he is.

264
00:20:14,303 --> 00:20:16,100
他肯定还有点儿值钱的
He's gotta have something.

265
00:20:16,271 --> 00:20:17,761
他就剩老婆和两个孩子了
He's got the two kids with her.

266
00:20:17,940 --> 00:20:21,603
他还有珍妮弗，那被他把肚子搞大的 可乐促销员
He's got Jennifer, the coke-dealing waitress that he knocked up.

267
00:20:21,778 --> 00:20:26,442
他还有4个从我妹妹车库里偷走的米其林轮胎
He's got four Michelin radials that he stole from my sister's garage.

268
00:20:27,750 --> 00:20:29,513
你出个价吧
Make an offer.

269
00:20:31,988 --> 00:20:36,322
我曾有个酒鬼老婆，她既年轻又漂亮
I had a wife who was a drunk. She was a beautiful girl, young girl.

270
00:20:36,493 --> 00:20:41,055
但就那样生活？后来有个戒酒计划 她参加了，戒了…2年
But live like that? Even they do a program... She did, I think, once, two years.

271
00:20:41,232 --> 00:20:43,223
后来计划没有了呢？别提了
And then they slip? Forget it.

272
00:20:43,400 --> 00:20:45,766
就像你身上捆着个炸弹
It's like you're strapped to a bomb.

273
00:20:46,770 --> 00:20:48,931
我还有多少时间？
What's my timeframe here?

274
00:20:49,740 --> 00:20:51,264
我不知道
I don't know.

275
00:20:51,443 --> 00:20:53,434
我想那不是个问题
I didn't think it'd be a problem.

276
00:20:55,080 --> 00:20:56,570
我会问问的
I'll ask.

277
00:21:24,111 --> 00:21:26,306
- 早啊，麦克 - 早，卡尔
- Hey, Michael. - Morning, Carl.

278
00:21:26,946 --> 00:21:28,946
肯纳、巴赫和莱迪恩律师事务所

279
00:21:34,554 --> 00:21:37,819
我不知道，戴尔，我不知道你想让我 施压到什么程度
I don't know. Del, I don't know how hard you want me to press here.

280
00:21:37,991 --> 00:21:39,982
让我知道他有多大能耐
Let me know how brave he wants to be.

281
00:21:40,161 --> 00:21:42,493
好吧，我现在还不知道他能有多能耐
Well, I'm not sure how brave he can be right now.

282
00:21:42,664 --> 00:21:44,996
我们只是刚刚确认了听证会的时间表
We just got a confirmation hearing scheduled.

283
00:21:45,166 --> 00:21:46,565
她有可能知道吗？
Any chance she knows that?

284
00:21:46,734 --> 00:21:50,363
喔，都上报了，谁知道呢？可能有人 读给她听吧
Well, it was in the paper. Who knows? Maybe she got someone to read it to her.

285
00:21:50,538 --> 00:21:53,063
她昨天给他老婆打电话了，打到他家里
She called his wife yesterday. She's calling his house.

286
00:21:53,241 --> 00:21:54,469
这可糟透了
This is a total nightmare.

287
00:21:54,643 --> 00:21:56,770
是的，我猜她无非是想要那套房子
Well, my guess is she's gonna want the condo.

288
00:21:56,946 --> 00:21:58,004
不是吧，那也太疯狂了
Come on, that's insane.

289
00:21:58,180 --> 00:22:01,707
好吧，我还能和你说什么呢？别和算计好了的 婊子斗
Well, what can I tell you? Don't piss off a motivated stripper.

290
00:22:01,884 --> 00:22:03,078
简直难以置信
It's just unbelievable.

291
00:22:03,252 --> 00:22:06,517
嗯，这样吧，了解他的底限，然后告诉我
All right. Well, find out his pain threshold and get back to me.

292
00:22:06,689 --> 00:22:08,589
或者你要他直接打电话给我
Or you can tell him to call me directly.

293
00:22:08,757 --> 00:22:10,748
好的，听你的，我来搞定
All right, I hear you. Let me get into it.

294
00:22:10,927 --> 00:22:12,087
好的，就这样，谢谢
Thanks.

295
00:22:12,262 --> 00:22:13,889
嘿，马蒂现在在哪儿？
Hey, where are we with Marty?

296
00:22:14,898 --> 00:22:16,388
我们给他留言了
We left word.

297
00:22:16,566 --> 00:22:18,727
等一下，再说一次，孩子有多大了？
Hold on. Go back. How old is the kid?

298
00:22:18,902 --> 00:22:20,893
他不是“孩子”了，都22了
He's not a kid. He's 22.

299
00:22:21,071 --> 00:22:22,732
- 是在迈阿密吗？ - 不是，比斯坎湾
- This is Miami? - Nope. Key Biscayne.

300
00:22:22,906 --> 00:22:24,396
他们指控他…
And they charged him.

301
00:22:24,574 --> 00:22:27,873
说他过失伤人，我的委托人…
Reckless endangerment. My client...

302
00:22:28,045 --> 00:22:33,483
我想他们实际上是想要…想要调查那名律师
I think really what they want, they want a reality check on the attorney down there.

303
00:22:33,651 --> 00:22:35,710
- 好吧 - 韦恩说你有些门路？
- Yeah. - Wayne said you have some connections?

304
00:22:35,886 --> 00:22:38,411
- 好的，让我拿支笔 - 谢谢
- Yeah, let me get a pen. - Thank you.

305
00:22:39,190 --> 00:22:42,216
现在，如果她直接给移民局打电话 那她就哪儿也去不了了
Now, if she calls the INS directly, she's gonna get nowhere.

306
00:22:42,394 --> 00:22:43,622
预约都不行么？
Even with the appointment?

307
00:22:43,795 --> 00:22:46,286
移民局是这么说的，埃文 就像被交通管制了一样
It's retail, Evan. It's like the DMV over there.

308
00:22:46,465 --> 00:22:49,798
除非能得到地区主管的同意，否则没人能离开
Unless they get a call from a district supervisor, then nobody moves.

309
00:22:49,968 --> 00:22:51,526
但你的人不是可以吗？
But your guy can do that?

310
00:22:51,703 --> 00:22:53,034
他已经离任了
He's a former commissioner.

311
