460
00:30:58,554 --> 00:31:00,454
- 我只是.... - 不好意思
- I'm just... - Excuse me.

461
00:31:00,623 --> 00:31:02,716
- 安娜，他们… - 他在做什么呀？
- Anna, they're... - What's he doing?

462
00:31:02,892 --> 00:31:05,588
对不起。她是…不，这是在作证，这是…
Excuse me. She's a... No, this is testimony. This is...

463
00:31:05,761 --> 00:31:07,752
对不起，我反对
Excuse me, I have an objection.

464
00:31:07,931 --> 00:31:10,297
你可以在这儿做个证人，你可以做个证人
You can be a witness here. You can be a witness.

465
00:31:10,467 --> 00:31:12,162
我不是证人，先生，我…
I am not a witness to this, sir, l...

466
00:31:12,335 --> 00:31:14,929
安娜，我爱你
Anna, I love you.

467
00:31:15,105 --> 00:31:20,008
我坐在这儿，认真听你说，我发誓…
And I'm sitting here and I'm listening to you and I swear...

468
00:31:20,176 --> 00:31:24,943
…我爱你胜过这世上的一切，这是属于我的时刻
...that I love you more than anything in the world. And this is my moment.

469
00:31:25,116 --> 00:31:28,916
这诡异的会议时刻
This strange conference-table moment.

470
00:31:29,086 --> 00:31:30,986
快把摄像机关了！
Turn off that camera!

471
00:31:31,556 --> 00:31:35,048
- 这是我的表白！ - 别关，把这些录下来！
- This is my offering! - No, I want this on the record!

472
00:31:35,226 --> 00:31:36,454
我到底关不关？
How do I turn it off?

473
00:31:36,627 --> 00:31:40,154
这就是我的供词，我的衣服就是供词 这就是我的耻辱
This is my offering. My clothes are my offering. This is my shame.

474
00:31:40,332 --> 00:31:43,096
我的资格！我被污辱了！
My credentials! I'm ashamed!

475
00:31:43,268 --> 00:31:46,669
我爱你，我向上帝发誓…
And I love you, and I swear to God...

476
00:31:54,380 --> 00:31:55,938
我想就这些
I guess that's it.

477
00:32:03,122 --> 00:32:04,419
我们什么时候能见到丹？
When do we get Don?

478
00:32:05,024 --> 00:32:07,549
她说争取半小时之内回来
She said to try back in half an hour.

479
00:32:07,727 --> 00:32:10,628
航班情况呢？机场情况怎么样？
And how about the flights? What's the story at O'Hare?

480
00:32:11,865 --> 00:32:14,493
- 四分钟前关闭了 - 该死
- Closed four minutes ago. - Shit.

481
00:32:15,869 --> 00:32:18,269
底特律的积雪已经有一英尺厚了
There is a foot of snow in Detroit already.

482
00:32:18,439 --> 00:32:20,703
托德，能给我来杯咖啡吗？
Todd, could I get that coffee now?

483
00:32:22,910 --> 00:32:27,040
他们从纽约派过来的是谁？克莱顿？没听说过
Who is this guy they sent from New York? Clayton? I never heard of him.

484
00:32:28,850 --> 00:32:30,283
麦克・雷蒙德・克莱顿
Michael Raymond Clayton.

485
00:32:30,452 --> 00:32:35,355
生于1959年9月9号，纽约布朗克斯区圣约瑟夫医院
Born September 9, 1959, St. Joseph's Hospital, Bronx, New York.

486
00:32:35,523 --> 00:32:39,220
父亲雷蒙德・沙维尔・克莱顿是纽约警局的巡警
Father is NYPD patrolman Raymond Xavier Clayton.

487
00:32:39,394 --> 00:32:42,056
母亲爱丽丝・玛丽・克莱顿
Mother, Alice Mary Clayton.

488
00:32:42,231 --> 00:32:45,394
1977年毕业于纽约奥伦奇郡的…
Graduates Washingtonville Central High School, Orange County, New York...

489
00:32:45,568 --> 00:32:47,195
…华盛顿中央高中
...in 1977.

490
00:32:47,370 --> 00:32:51,739
1980年毕业于圣・约翰大学，82年福特汉姆 法学院毕业
Graduates St. John's University, 1980. Fordham Law, '82.

491
00:32:52,408 --> 00:32:56,902
82到86年，在皇后区司法部门担任助理检察官
'82 through '86, he's ADA with the Queens district attorney's office.

492
00:32:57,079 --> 00:33:00,014
1986年，他加入了曼哈顿―皇后区…
1986, he's with the Joint Manhattan-Queens...

493
00:33:00,183 --> 00:33:02,117
…有组织犯罪特别小组
...Organized Crime Task Force.

494
00:33:02,285 --> 00:33:05,686
1990年，他开始在肯纳、巴赫和莱迪恩 律师事务所工作
And then in 1990, he starts at Kenner, Bach & Ledeen.

495
00:33:05,856 --> 00:33:07,289
那么他是合伙人喽？
So he's a partner?

496
00:33:08,191 --> 00:33:10,682
不，他被列为特约顾问
No. He's listed as special counsel.

497
00:33:10,861 --> 00:33:12,886
上面写了他的专长是遗产法和信托法
Says he specializes in wills and trusts.

498
00:33:13,798 --> 00:33:16,426
他从刑事诉讼转型到遗产法和信托法？
He goes from criminal prosecution to wills and trusts?

499
00:33:16,601 --> 00:33:18,967
他在那里干了17年了，还不是合伙人？
He's been there 17 years, he's not a partner?

500
00:33:19,137 --> 00:33:22,800
这就是他们派来的人？这家伙到底是谁？
This is the guy they send? Who is this guy?

501
00:33:37,056 --> 00:33:39,320
- 你好 - 把门关好
- Hi. - Close the door.

502
00:33:39,792 --> 00:33:43,785
好，你们当中没有人知道他来了吧？
All right. So nobody, none of you, had any idea he was coming?

503
00:33:44,363 --> 00:33:46,228
去密尔沃基？去听证会？
To Milwaukee? For a deposition?

504
00:33:46,399 --> 00:33:49,960
我们以为已经解决了，有一些传言 所以我们觉得事情已经妥了
We thought there was a settlement. There's been some rumors.

505
00:33:50,136 --> 00:33:54,732
是这样，这事非常简单，亚瑟没有按量服药
Okay. Look, it's very simple. Arthur has a chemical imbalance.

506
00:33:54,908 --> 00:33:58,776
他应该坚持吃药，但他没有
He's supposed to be taking his medication. He's fallen behind on that.

507
00:33:58,945 --> 00:34:01,436
现在他正在好转中，三四天后他就会好的
He's on the mend. He'll be fine in three or four days.

508
00:34:01,615 --> 00:34:05,779
现在，我给你们说清楚 这屋子里发生的一切都不要透露出去
Now, I wanna make this crystal clear. What happened here stays in this room.

509
00:34:05,953 --> 00:34:08,922
一点一滴信息都不能泄露
This is not a piece of information you wanna be out in front of.

510
00:34:09,090 --> 00:34:12,389
还有人有问题吗，有就马上说
Anybody has a problem with that, I need to know right now.

511
00:34:13,527 --> 00:34:14,892
很好
All right.

512
00:34:15,763 --> 00:34:17,594
我们今晚就得在这儿过了
We're stuck here overnight.

513
00:34:17,766 --> 00:34:20,064
如果可能的话我明天就送他回家
I'm gonna take him home tomorrow if I can.

514
00:34:20,235 --> 00:34:22,203
谁负责听证会的时间表？
Who's in charge of the deposition schedule?

515
00:34:22,370 --> 00:34:24,031
- 我 - 我们现在进行到什么程度了？
- I am. - Where do we stand with that?

516
00:34:24,206 --> 00:34:26,401
我想我们可能停住了，我们不知道下一步 该做些什么
I guess it's on hold. We didn't know what to do.

517
00:34:26,575 --> 00:34:28,634
没有停下来的事，你继续做你们该做的
Nothing is on hold. Keep doing what you were.

518
00:34:28,810 --> 00:34:31,074
对方想谈些什么的话，他们可以纽约打电话
Other side wants to talk, they can call New York.

519
00:34:31,246 --> 00:34:34,306
- 我要他的公文包 - 亚瑟的？不知道…没看见
- I need his briefcase. - Arthur's? I don't... I didn't see it.

520
00:34:34,484 --> 00:34:37,578
- 他说就在房间里 - 可能朱迪拿走了吧
- He said it was in the room. - It might be the stuff Jody grabbed.

521
00:34:37,954 --> 00:34:39,546
找到它
Find it.

522
00:34:45,528 --> 00:34:49,828
所有这些人，都开始有这些梦了，对吧？
So all these people, they all start having these dreams, okay?

523
00:34:50,000 --> 00:34:54,403
你知道什么叫“幻象探索”么？嗯，就像那些 纳瓦霍人（美洲印第安人的一支）那样
You know what a vision quest is? You know, for, like, Navajos and stuff?

524
00:34:54,571 --> 00:34:57,836
嗯，我知道，就像…
Yeah. I think so. Like a...

525
00:34:58,208 --> 00:35:00,073
就像一个特别的梦
Like a special dream.

526
00:35:00,244 --> 00:35:04,806
不同之处就在于所有人都做一样的梦
Except this is like a whole bunch of people having the same dream.

527
00:35:04,983 --> 00:35:08,384
这个梦让他们大家都到同一个地方
They're all having this dream that they should go to this one place.

528
00:35:08,553 --> 00:35:10,578
他们不知道为什么要这样做
They don't know why or anything.

529
00:35:10,755 --> 00:35:13,883
但他们就是有种非去那里不可的感觉
They just have this feeling that they have to go there.

530
00:35:14,058 --> 00:35:15,923
他们是召唤的一群人
That they've been summoned.

531
00:35:16,094 --> 00:35:17,322
那就是其中的一章
That's the chapter.

532
00:35:17,495 --> 00:35:20,464
真的，就叫做“召唤与征服”
Seriously, that's what it's called: "Summons to Conquest."

533
00:35:20,633 --> 00:35:21,930
这是标题
That's the title.

534
00:35:22,101 --> 00:35:27,767
嗯，但他们知道么？他们知道他们的梦 都一样吗？
Yeah, but do they know? Do they know they're all having the same dream?

535
00:35:27,940 --> 00:35:29,908
不知道，这就是精彩的地方
No. That's what's so cool.

536
00:35:30,442 --> 00:35:32,376
他们都觉得只有自己才有
They all think it's just them.

537
00:35:32,545 --> 00:35:36,606
也许他们可能已经疯了，但他们就是不想承认
That maybe they're, like, going crazy or something, so they don't wanna admit it.

538
00:35:36,783 --> 00:35:38,910
是呀，但其实他们没有发疯，对吗？
Yeah, but they're not crazy, are they?

539
00:35:39,085 --> 00:35:42,577
不，一切都是真的，他们没有疯
No. It's real. It's really happening.

540
00:35:42,756 --> 00:35:46,385
是的，都是真的，不是么？
Yeah, it is happening, isn't it?

541
00:35:47,594 --> 00:35:52,258
有东西比他们更为强大，而他们还没有准备好…
Something larger than themselves and they're not ready, are they...

542
00:35:52,433 --> 00:35:54,230
…他们会察觉到么？
...to hear it?

543
00:35:54,402 --> 00:35:56,302
是的，不久之后他们就会
Yeah. But later they will.

544
00:35:56,470 --> 00:35:59,303
如果你想看这本书的话，我就不再透露情节了
So if you're gonna read it, I don't wanna spoil it.

545
00:36:00,908 --> 00:36:02,739
你在干什么，和谁说话呢？
What are you doing? Who you talking to?

546
00:36:02,910 --> 00:36:04,878
我给我爸爸打电话，他的一个朋友接的
I called my dad. It's a friend of his.

547
00:36:05,046 --> 00:36:08,311
- 谁？ - 伊顿先生，你不认识他
- Who? - Mr. Edens. You don't know him.

548
00:36:08,483 --> 00:36:11,145
- 喂，喂 - 亨利，已经11点多了
- Hello? Hello? - Henry, it's after 11.

549
00:36:11,320 --> 00:36:13,117
我得马上挂了
I gotta get off now.

550
00:36:13,288 --> 00:36:17,281
不，等下，那本书，我想看看，书名是什么
No. Wait, wait. The book. I need the book. The title.

551
00:36:17,893 --> 00:36:20,123
书名是 《王国与征服》
The book is Realm and Conquest.

552
00:36:20,295 --> 00:36:22,058
《王国与征服》
Realm and Conquest.

553
00:36:22,231 --> 00:36:25,291
- 单行本，红色封面的 - 亨利，把电话给我
- It's Book One, with the red cover. - Henry, give me the phone.

554
00:36:25,468 --> 00:36:28,028
我得挂了，告诉我爸我给他打电话了，好吗？
I gotta go. Tell my dad I called. Okay?

555
00:36:28,905 --> 00:36:33,308
好，好的，谢…谢，谢谢你，亨利，谢谢你
Yeah. Yeah. Thank... Thank... Thank... Thank you, Henry, thank you.

556
00:36:37,513 --> 00:36:40,949
《王国与征服》，谢谢
Realm and Conquest. Thank you.

557
00:37:04,175 --> 00:37:06,200
凯伦？你好，我是麦克・克莱顿
Karen? Hi, I'm Michael Clayton.

558
00:37:06,378 --> 00:37:07,845
- 你迟到了 - 我知道
- You're late. - I know.

559
00:37:08,013 --> 00:37:10,538
对不起，这事比我们预想的要复杂
I'm sorry, it was more complicated than we thought.

560
00:37:10,716 --> 00:37:12,411
他在哪儿？五点半我们就在这儿了
Where is he? We've been here since 5:30.

561
00:37:12,585 --> 00:37:14,746
- 他睡了 - 那么，把他叫起来
- He's asleep. - Well, wake him up.

562
00:37:14,921 --> 00:37:17,185
那可不行，我们刚让他安静下来
That's not gonna happen. We just got him sedated.

563
00:37:17,690 --> 00:37:20,716
只要他接受日常的药物治疗…
Once he gets back on his regular medication...

564
00:37:20,893 --> 00:37:22,827
…不多时间他就能回来
...then it's just a matter of time.

565
00:37:22,995 --> 00:37:25,759
- 你有看那段录像么？那盘带子？ - 我听说了
- Have you seen the video? The tape? - I heard about it.

566
00:37:26,033 --> 00:37:28,501
那之后发生的事情更糟
What happened after is worse.

567
00:37:28,669 --> 00:37:32,571
那可是停车场，人们停车开车的地方
This is in the parking lot, okay? People running for their cars.

568
00:37:32,739 --> 00:37:34,866
他在那里就穿了双袜子，别的没了
He's there in his socks, nothing else.

569
00:37:35,042 --> 00:37:38,705
“对不起，很抱歉，我再也不想和这疾病为伍了
"I'm sorry. I'm so sorry. I will not sit with this sickness any longer.

570
00:37:38,879 --> 00:37:41,677
我再也不能助长这疾病了”
I cannot aid this sickness any longer."

571
00:37:41,849 --> 00:37:43,441
这话什么意思？
What does this mean?

572
00:37:43,851 --> 00:37:45,409
我也不清楚
I'm not sure.

573
00:37:45,586 --> 00:37:48,214
你整晚和他在一起，他说了些什么？
You've been with him the whole evening. What's he saying?

574
00:37:48,389 --> 00:37:50,186
他没说什么有用的
He wasn't really making much sense.

575
00:37:50,358 --> 00:37:51,916
你这解释我可不能接受
This is totally unacceptable.

576
00:37:52,093 --> 00:37:55,028
这可是价值30亿美元的集体诉讼
This is a 3-billion-dollar class-action lawsuit.

577
00:37:55,196 --> 00:37:57,130
到了早上，我不得不给我老板汇报
In the morning, I have to call my board.

578
00:37:57,299 --> 00:38:01,861
告诉他们我们这案子的首席辩护律师被逮逋了
I have to tell them that the architect of our entire defense has been arrested...

579
00:38:02,038 --> 00:38:06,202
…因为他在暴风雪中裸奔，并在停车场追赶原告
...for running naked in a snowstorm, chasing the plaintiffs through a parking lot.

580
00:38:06,376 --> 00:38:08,173
我能理解
I understand.

581
00:38:09,245 --> 00:38:11,270
他说的那疾病到底是什么？
What sickness is he talking about?

582
00:38:11,448 --> 00:38:14,076
- 不知道，可能是什么别的东西 - 那好，是什么？
- I don't know. It could be anything. - Well, give me one.

583
00:38:14,250 --> 00:38:15,547
冻伤吧
Frostbite.

584
00:38:16,052 --> 00:38:17,679
你觉得这很好玩吗？
You think this is funny?

585
00:38:17,855 --> 00:38:20,119
你看，他的妻子病了，去年去世的
Look, his wife was sick and she died last year.

586
00:38:20,291 --> 00:38:24,751
他的女儿不理他了，他很孤独，他现在的 生活就只有你的案子
His daughter doesn't talk to him. He's all alone. All he does is your case.

587
00:38:24,929 --> 00:38:27,625
他忘了吃药，度过了糟糕的一天，仅此而已
He skipped his pills. He had a bad day. That's it.

588
00:38:27,798 --> 00:38:30,494
看来你是这方面的权威喽？
And you're somehow the authority on this?

589
00:38:31,202 --> 00:38:33,727
他上次发病是在八年前，当时我在场
His last episode was eight years ago. I was there.

590
00:38:33,905 --> 00:38:36,738
我帮他回到家，看着他好转，就这样
I helped bring him home. I watched him get better. That's it.

591
00:38:36,908 --> 00:38:40,674
行了，凯伦，你雇佣他不是因为他有抑郁证
Come on, Karen, you didn't hire this guy because of his low-key regularity...

592
00:38:40,846 --> 00:38:43,838
…你雇他是因为他是最棒的，因为他的才智…
...you hired him because he's a killer, because he's brilliant...

593
00:38:44,016 --> 00:38:46,678
…因为他在这个案子上足够执着努力…
...because he's crazy enough to grind away on this case...

594
00:38:46,852 --> 00:38:49,616
- …6年来无休止地工作着 - 打断下，我们可是给了他工钱的
...for six years without a break. - We pay for his time.

595
00:38:49,789 --> 00:38:51,814
我知道你想要个解释
I thought you wanted an explanation.

596
00:38:51,991 --> 00:38:54,721
到了早上，我会给马蒂・巴赫打电话的
In the morning, I'm calling Marty Bach.

597
00:38:54,894 --> 00:38:57,920
然后么，你也知道的，谢谢你，麦克
But, then, you know that. Thank you, Michael.

598
00:39:03,803 --> 00:39:05,896
他大部分时候很平静
He was mostly just quiet.

599
00:39:06,073 --> 00:39:08,940
我听到他的动静，15分钟前我给他吃了药
I heard him moving around, I gave him a pill 15 minutes ago.

600
00:39:09,109 --> 00:39:11,600
- 他吃了？ - 说到做到，对吧？
- He took it? - A deal's a deal, right?

601
00:39:11,779 --> 00:39:13,508
干的不错，埃斯顿
A super job, Elston.

602
00:39:13,680 --> 00:39:17,343
你去纽约吧，如果需要入场券或其它什么东西 和我说就行
You get to New York, you need tickets to the game or anything, you let me know.

603
00:39:17,518 --> 00:39:18,951
我会把这事办好的
I'll do that for sure.

604
00:39:39,341 --> 00:39:40,968
你见过她了吗？
Did you see her?

605
00:39:41,310 --> 00:39:43,471
- 谁？ - 安娜
- Who? - Anna.

606
00:39:44,013 --> 00:39:45,412
没有
No.

607
00:39:46,615 --> 00:39:50,142
没有，我没见到她，她可能回农场了
No, I didn't see her. She probably went back to the farm.

608
00:39:51,020 --> 00:39:52,681
嗯，我们需要她
Well, we need her.

609
00:39:54,524 --> 00:39:59,325
